<b>BABYVR TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF USE</b>

<b>1. Introduction</b>
These Terms and Conditions of Use regulate the rules to which the use of the following product by ViRe Instruments, S.L. (hereinafter, the Company) is subject.

The Company has developed a non-medical product that:

- Allows visualization of 4D/5D prenatal ultrasounds in three formats: Hyperrealism (printed, on a screen and/or any other 2D format), Virtual Reality, and Augmented Reality (hereinafter, referred to as "XR Hyperrealism").

- Is marketed together with cardboard glasses (hereinafter referred to as "VR Goggles") and a "marker" type card (hereinafter referred to as "AR Card").

- Operates via one-time fee payment by the end-user through a cloud platform (hereinafter referred to as “Platform”) consisting of a website and a mobile application (hereinafter referred to as “App”).

- Is named BabyVR (hereinafter referred to as the "Product").

The purchase of the Product and/or the download or use of the App attributes the status of User to the person who does so and implies the acceptance of all the conditions included in this document and in the Privacy Policy, Intellectual and Industrial Property Policy, and the Legal Notice of said website and mobile application.

